{
  "name": "Knowledge Score Update",
  "version": "3.1.0",
  "description": "After any tool use: update .knowledge/ scores and capture new patterns. Works for all roles and all knowledge domains.",
  "when": {
    "type": "postToolUse",
    "toolTypes": ["*"]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Find workspace root by locating the folder that contains .kiro/hooks/ directory. Check if this tool execution produced a scoreable outcome:\n\nSCORE UP (+0.5): tool succeeded AND result was used (file written, decision made, output accepted)\nSCORE DOWN (-1.0): tool failed AND failure was caused by a known knowledge item (template, lesson, rule)\nCAPTURE: if tool result revealed a new pattern, insight, rule, or knowledge not yet in .knowledge/ → auto-capture\n\nDomain mapping (match by topic, create new domain if none fit):\n- coding/implementation → ui, sync, web\n- testing/qa → web\n- design/ux → ui\n- hooks/agent/memory/tooling → tooling\n- law/legal/compliance → legal\n- accounting/finance/tax/investment → finance\n- computer science/algorithms/data structures → cs\n- AI/ML/LLM concepts → ai\n- anything else → use topic name as domain id (e.g. 'biology', 'marketing')\n\nIf score change: update utility_score in {root}/.knowledge/index.json for matching domain.\nIf new domain needed: add it to {root}/.knowledge/index.json domains array first.\nIf new pattern/insight: append to matching *LessonsIndex.json (create file+index if domain is new) with fields: id, type, summary, detail, source, timestamp, effectiveness:{applied_count:0,prevented_failures:0,still_relevant:true,confidence:0.75}, auto_captured:true. Skip if duplicate.\nSilent always."
  }
}
